sec.p:
A fragment of the 5′ untranslated region of hAKR1D1 (5β-reductase) representing the region –383 to +446 kb (relative to transcription start site) [21] was cloned from RPCI-11 HS BAC clone 386M10 (Invitrogen, UK). A construct was generated using high-fidelity PCR amplification using the following oligonucleotides, incorporating a Kpn site (underlined) and confirmatory sequencing performed.
5′AKR1D1 (−383), GGTACCAGTCCTGCTGCATCCAAATC;
3′AKR1D1 (+446) GGTACCTGTGGAGAACCTGACTGTAGGA.
